name: sfchronicle
text: A deadly coronavirus outbreak looked inevitable in March for Laguna Honda, the largest nursing home in the state. Residents felt scared. Workers were frightened too. But no residents or workers have died of COVID-19. Here's how they did it. https://t.co/p6PdOOX1ss

name: sfchronicle
text:
California will add resources to fight coronavirus surge in the Central Valley, Newsom says.

The rate of positive tests there is higher than the state average, ranging from 11% in Fresno County to nearly 18% in Tulare and Stanislaus counties. https://t.co/AW4uuZzJHR
